# INTENT PLANNING LAYER

Do not generate code in this layer.

This layer extracts user intent and converts it into a structured internal design plan.

---

# STEP 1 — EXTRACT INTENT

Identify:

- Section purpose (hero / continuation / feature / editorial / CTA / grid)
- Relative importance (primary / secondary / supporting)
- Dominance level (high / medium / low)
- Layout direction (horizontal / vertical / grid / centered)
- Ratio (if mentioned)
- Height behavior (auto / tall / full viewport)
- Mobile expectation
- Tone (minimal / bold / refined / corporate)

---

# HARD vs SOFT CONSTRAINT CLASSIFICATION

## Hard Constraints (Never Override)

If explicitly mentioned:

- Layout direction (left/right, side-by-side, two-column)
- Ratio (50/50, 60/40, etc.)
- Height (full height / viewport)
- Order (image left, text right)

These must be locked and passed downstream.

---

## Soft Preferences (May Refine Later)

- Density
- Typography scale
- Visual mood
- Spacing tone

---

# DIRECTION LOCK RULE

If prompt contains:

- "left and right"
- "side by side"
- "two column"
- "split layout"

Then:

Layout direction = horizontal (locked)
Vertical stacking on desktop is prohibited.

---

# BUILD INTERNAL DESIGN PLAN

Define internally:

- Archetype
- Column count
- Ratio
- Height logic
- Alignment
- Density profile
- Mobile collapse behavior

Do not proceed without a coherent plan.

---

# VALIDATION BEFORE HANDOFF

Confirm:

- Hard constraints preserved
- Dominance matches section purpose
- Mobile behavior defined
- Layout direction locked if explicit

Then pass to structural layer.